[SN]TITLE[SN]
Pistyll woman admits 'naked horse riding' ad harassment

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A Gwynedd woman who advertised naked horse riding in the name of a former friend has been ordered to carry out 200 hours of unpaid work.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Erika Benedikta, 51, left posters offering the service at a cafe and a farm, and also sent abusive messages.
Benedikta, of Pistyll, Pwllheli, admitted harassment at Caernarfon Magistrates' Court on Friday.
She was also ordered to pay Â£370 in compensation and costs and handed a three-year restraining order.
